Don't think I'll be going back in a hurry! Sunday, June 10th 2018 Not Just A Freak Between The Sheets. Thats right, by night I am a freak between the sheets, but during the morning I'm much more...calm lol. I love to read the daily news, gossip and fashion articles in the morning over a cup of coffee and some tasty breakfast, or if its cold... underneath the duvet of my cosy bed.

I like to see what is currently going on in around the world, It can be very interesting and I think its great to be in tune and up to date about current world affairs. On a lighter note, I also enjoy reading the not so serious gossip columns. I like a bit of drama, I find the lives some of these celebrities lead to be so extravagant...I'm jealous!

Browsing some of the new fashionable clothing, shoes and accessories too is also worth my total attention, I like to keep up to do with fashion and look my best, especially when I know I've got pleasant, horny company turning up quite regularly! Wednesday, April 11th 2018 Preparation For Sunny Days. I think in the last week or so it has became apparent to me that we are now not far from weekly hot sunshine... and that means... Its gonna be healthy eating and more working out from now, because I wanna look my best for summer! Thursday, March 15th 2018 Is Breakfast Really Healthy? As you can see, I am a skinny girl, slim, sexy but nice curves. I have toyed with the idea of pushing myself to eat breakfast, even when I don't really feel hungry. I have also fasted and avoided it completely. I think it's a personal choice but here are some of my views about it.

1. Breakfast Doesn’t Increase Your Metabolism.

Your metabolic rate increases slightly when you fast.

2. Breakfast Doesn’t Stop Muscle Breakdown. Starvation mode is a myth: you won’t lose muscle if you don’t eat every 3 hours as long as you do regular exercise.

3. Breakfast Doesn’t Manage Blood Sugar Well.

Insulin is key for muscle growth but is also responsible for fat storage. Fasting reduces your insulin levels and increases insulin sensitivity dramatically more than eating small frequent meals do.

4. Breakfast Increases Hunger. Many people feel hungrier during the day after eating breakfast. Great for Weight Gain If you’re skinny person who struggles to eat a lot, eating breakfast will make it easier to reach your caloric needs. Not So Great for Fat Loss. Especially since more frequent meals don’t increase your metabolism.

5. Breakfast Is Not Healthier. People who don’t eat breakfast are usually the ones who don’t exercise and who grab a donut on their way to work, eat junk food at noon and a big dinner in front of the TV.

6. Breakfast Impairs Concentration.

You don’t need breakfast for mental alertness. A lot of people, especially students, skip breakfast because they know they’ll be more productive, concentrated and motivated during the rest of the day as a result. I’ve experienced the same thing.

7. Breakfast Is Unnatural. Our ancestors probably didn’t eat large breakfasts: they’d have to hunt it first (unless we’re talking left-overs). Hunter-gather meal patterns with large dinners and little during the day seem more natural.
